p.font: During the upgrade we rely on LensV2UpgradeContract that has all parameters immutable and is able to control ProxyAdmin contract to perform an upgrade.

div.p: ProxyAdmin contract splits the permissions between Owner and ControllerContract for additional security.

p.font: ProxyAdmin contract is used as a relay to TransparentProxy, allowing its MultiSig Owner to upgrade, rollback upgrade and change the ProxyAdmin.
At the same time it is allowing ControllerContract only to perform an upgrade and clear itself from controller permissions afterwards.

div.p: LensV2UpgradeContract has all the upgrade parameters immutable.

Immutability of parameters allows to check and verify the upgrade setup on-chain before performing an actual upgrade and eliminates any chances of manual mistakes when signing parametrized transactions.
